# Build outputs: `nix build` / `nixos-rebuild build` drop a ./result symlink
result
result-*

# VM disk images created by `nixos-rebuild build-vm` (run from the repo dir)
*.qcow2

# Direnv, if you ever adopt it
.direnv/

# Machine-derived DMS fragments: outputs.lua (Displays GUI — THIS machine's
# monitors) and colors.lua (matugen — THIS machine's wallpaper palette).
# Syncing them between hosts would apply one machine's monitors/palette to
# the other, so they're local-only; home/dms.nix's activation script seeds
# them empty on a fresh clone (require() hard-fails on a missing file, but
# an empty Lua chunk is fine). The other five fragments stay tracked —
# they're shared preferences.
home/hypr/dms/outputs.lua
home/hypr/dms/colors.lua
